I've been playing RTS games for more than 25 years (with Age of Empires I being my first). Fast-forward to nowadays, and Age of Empires IV is a serious contender for being my favorite of the genre. I'll list some of the things I love about this game:
- Historical immersion: each civilization is intricately crafted, reflecting that people's architectural and military achievements during the High and Late Middle Ages;
- Rich roster of asymmetric civilizations;
- Superb sound design;
- Pleasant visuals;
- Refinement of the "Age" formula to perfection;
- The Crucible (included with Dynasties of the East DLC).

